Finally, I found a solution to all of the above problems. The ordergreat(x, y) command must be placed before simp: false, otherwise it does not work. Here is the latest version of the function in the Question variables section: 
```text
rewrite_with_surd(expr) := block([base, exponent, pow_num, non_sqrt, new_args, second_arg],
    if atom(expr) then return(expr),
    if op(expr) = "^" then (
        base: part(expr, 1),
        exponent: part(expr, 2),
        if ratnump(exponent) and denom(exponent) = 2 then (
            pow_num: num(exponent),
            non_sqrt: ev(base^floor(pow_num/2), simp),
            return(non_sqrt*rat(sqrt(base)))
        )
    ),
    new_args: map(rewrite_with_surd, args(expr)),
    /* If the expression is in the form a*(b*sqrt(c)) return it as (a*b)*sqrt(c) */
    if length(new_args) = 2 and not atom(second(new_args)) then (
        second_arg: args(second(new_args)),
        if not atom(second_arg) and 
           op(expr) = "*" and op(second(new_args)) = "*" then (
            return(ev(first(new_args)*first(second_arg), simp)*second(second_arg))
        )
    ),
    return(apply(op(expr), new_args))
);

ordergreat(x, y, z);
expr1: 3*2^((2+3)/2);
expr2: (1 + 2*(x + y)^((2+3)/2)) / z;
```
 And its use in the Question text section: 
```text
<div style="display: none;">{@simp: false@}</div>
<p>Original: {@expr1@}, Rewritten: {@rewrite_with_surd(expr1)@}</p>
<p>Original: {@expr2@}, Rewritten: {@rewrite_with_surd(expr2)@}</p>
<p>[​[input:ans1]​] [​[validation:ans1]​]</p>
```

